      "This is a question we hear often from people planning a Sri Lanka trip who want to dive. Both regions are good options. The right choice depends almost entirely on when you are visiting and what you want from the experience.",
      "Trincomalee: the case for. HMS Hermes is the reason Trincomalee sits in a different category from most Sri Lankan dive destinations. A 182-metre aircraft carrier wreck at 35 metres, largely intact, covered in coral after 80 years underwater. Nothing else in Sri Lanka competes with this. Add Pigeon Island's reef sharks and hawksbill turtles, the blue whale watching in March and April, and the overall quality of a less-developed dive destination, and Trincomalee is the choice for serious divers or anyone who wants a centrepiece dive experience.",
