      "Hikkaduwa: the case against. The best sites are busy. In peak tourist season (December to January), dive sites are noticeably crowded. Visibility averages 10-15 metres, good but not the 20-30 metres Trincomalee delivers in peak season. There is no equivalent to HMS Hermes. The dive infrastructure is more commercialised, with higher diver-to-instructor ratios and faster turnarounds.",
      "Our verdict. If your travel window is May to October and diving quality matters to you, Trincomalee is the better choice, and not by a small margin. If your trip falls in November to April or you are already on the south coast, Hikkaduwa is good and worth doing. Some travellers manage both by doing the south coast first (October to April), then returning to Trincomalee from May onward.",
